Scenario 1: Stock Trading Platform

Ultra-low latency --
10 m+ concurrent traders
Critical: No missed trades
Updates: 100 times per second

Trade-off Analysis:
Websocket
Bidirectional (traders can place orders)
✅ Low latency (10-50ms
❌ Memory: 50k connections = 400MB server memory
❌ Complexity: Connection management, load balancing
❌ Risk: Connection drops = missed trade


Option B: UDP + TCP Hybrid